  <description><![CDATA[<p>Ski Kirchberg! Nestled among the peaks of the Kitzbüheler Alps is the world renowned Kitzbühel/Kirchberg ski area. The lively town of Kirchberg has its own local slopes on Gaisberg, where the nursery slopes are served by the Gaisberg and Maierl chairlifts close to the resort centre. There’s also local night skiing from the top of the main Gaisberg lift. The town is just 6km west of the internationally celebrated medieval town of Kitzbühel, and there are bus links with the huge Kitzbühel ski area. Here, modern cable cars and lifts take skiers to the famous Hahnenkamm and Kitzbühelerhorn areas, along with links to Jochberg and Pass Thurn. Kirchberg has an action-packed snowboard fun-park, and extensive snow-making facilities. There’s also a connection from Kirchberg into the vast Ski Welt area via Westendorf.</p>]]></description>
