  <generalInformation><![CDATA[<p><strong>Beginners</strong> can start off on the gentle slopes of Kirchberg’s own mountain, Gaisberg, whereby the nursery lifts operate free-of-charge, perfect for a beginner’s skiing holiday. There is a selection of gentle nursery slopes to choose from and the local ski school will help build your confidence up for the more challenging runs.</p>
<p><strong>Intermediates</strong> Head to the Kitzbüheler Horn or the Hahnenkamm where there are plenty of long runs, steep slopes and mogul fields. If you’re feeling adventurous on your ski holiday, then why not try out the Ski Safari which offers a day of skiing on a 35 km continuous trail. Or you could ski near the resort where you will find a wide range of blue and red runs and steep descents.</p>
<p><strong>Advanced</strong> From Kirchberg you can ski the world-famous Streif on Hahnenkamm or purchase the Kitzbüheler Alps AllStarCard which opens up the possibility of skiing 1088kms of slopes. One of the best off-piste areas is at Pass Thurn, modern lifts carry skiers towards the Resterhöhe area for some of the finest skiing in the region.</p>
<p><strong>Snowboarding</strong> Kirchberg is also a first rate snowboarding holiday destination with terrain to suit all levels of ability and a snowboarding park where you can practice your tricks at Pass Thurn.</p>]]></generalInformation>
